<Author>SanDiegoErik
<Content>Be careful with room selection We just got back from our second stay at the HGVC HHV. This is a nice resort significantly set apart from most of the hotels on Wakiki. This is a good thing for us, as we don't necessarily like the chaos of central Wakiki and you do get a little more space on the beach down on the HHV end. It's also nice to have a selection of pools areas to choose from.The bad stuff - ElevatorsThere are clearly not enough elevators for this building. The wait can be extreme around check-out/in times.The PoolIt's tiny. Both time that we've been there, there were too many people in the pool and a few of them were smoking (dropping their ashes into the water).ParkingYou have to pay extra for it.The GymYou have to pay extra for it.LaundryIt's not in the unit.The Good Stuff - HHVIt's part of HHV, so you can charge things to your room, get room service and enjoy the facilities in the whole complex.ComfortThe rooms are comfortably outfitted and well maintained. For a timeshare, it is surprising to find that the beds were not terribly uncomfortable.The only other thing that I can add is that you really need to be careful about the room you select. The standard rooms are all on the back side of the building. They have just broken ground on a new HGVC tower that will be alarmingly close to these buildings. I suspect that there will be a lot of noise for the next couple of years and then neigbors that can look into your windows pretty easily. The ocean view rooms are on the opposite side. They more appropriately have an ocean peak, but do not have the problems associated with the other side. The ocean front rooms are on the end of the building and have an unobstructed, fairly spectacular view. 
