<Content>Have Stayed at Better Resorts First trip to Hawaii, stayed at the Lagoon Tower with partial ocean view. Have stayed at many timeshare units before and the quality of this unit does not stand out. It was clean and neat but does not warrant spending an extra $20,000 over other timeshares. They try to sell you on the Hilton name but we had the same issues trying to book this one as we do other timeshares and once you enter the unit it looks the same as most other timeshares.The sand on the beach was nice but having to pay $30 for a beach umbrella and $13 for a chair is a joke. The water was a bit cold and it got really deep really fast, Waikiki is not the best beach in the world.If renting a car, order online at thrifty and pick it up at the Radison on Al Lamona avenue behind the hotel, this way you will save a bundle compared to any other rental agency. I also did not like having to pay for parking at the resort, but was told that all hotels will charge in Waikiki.Check out the International marketplace (flea market) across from the cheesecake factory on the main strip for great deals. Don't miss the Wailana Coffee House for breakfast, good food and cheap. 
