<Author>BradnCheryl
<Content>Loved our 1 week stay in the Kalia Tower We just returned from a 2 - week vacation in Hawaii. We spent the 1st week (5/14/05 - 5/21/05) in a 1 BR HGVC condo on the 17th floor, in the Kalia Tower. The condo was beautiful, we had an ocean view,  the Kalia Pool on the 4th floor was directly below our balconies. It was great just sitting out on our balconies enjoying the view of Waikiki Beach, the Rainbow Tower  the lagoon. The free washers  dryers happened to be across the hall, just outside the door of our condo. We enjoyed the shopping available on the Hilton property. We stopped at the Mandara Spa Store in the shopping area  even got 10 minute back  neck massages there, without an appointment! There is an ABC Store in the shopping area, where you can pickup convenience food, souveniers, etc. Our family loved the penquins, fish ponds, flamingos  the waterfalls in the resort. We really enjoyed our days spent on Waikiki Beach. We took our own beach mats, chairs  umbrella, to avoid paying the resort rentals. The Amercian Express desk was very helpful in booking our luau (Paradise Cove). We had a rental van, it cost $13 per day to keep it in the parking garage.Went snorkeling at Haunama Bay, beach hopping around the island, visited Ala Moana Mall  Pearl Harbor. Unfortunately, one person in our party got ill during our stay. However, she was able to see the Dr on property 1st thing the following morning. We can't wait to return to the Hilton Hawaiian Village, we had a fabulous time, absolutely no complaints. 
