<Author>gjones16
<Content>Unforgettable Vacation!!! This was our first visit to Hawaii and we stayed at the Lagoon Towers in a 2 BR/2BA villa, March 26 - April 1, 2005 (Spring Break). The units were well equipped for a family vacation. The kitchen had granite countertops, and well appointed appliances. The master bedroom had a king size bed and the 2nd bedroom had 2 full size beds. Both bathrooms were large and exceptional clean. Washer/dryer are on each floor, but not in the room. The unit was facing the ocean, so every morning you awake to the beautiful sounds coming off of the beach. I got up early one morning a took a quiet stroll on the beach. It was heavenly. Words could not express the tranquility you feel, just walking around looking at the water.Wakiki Beach is located in the city, so there's something for everyone.We ate at many of the restaurants on and around the Hilton property. We loved the shopping and the various sights on the island.I didn't mention a lot of things about our trip, but I will say that this has been one of the memorable moments in my life. I'm already planning our next trip.Gwen Jones 
